{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## What\n\nThe central index `docs/README.md` is incomplete (4 living/normative docs unlinked) and\nmixes living reference docs with historical evidence with no visual/structural\ndistinction. Complete the index and add a taxonomy — **in place, WITHOUT relocating any\nfiles.**\n\nVerified state (`origin/main`): exactly four `docs/*.md` are unlinked from the index —\n`attest-substrate.md` (living developer API ref), `review-policy.md` (normative policy),\n`session-id-shims.md` (living reference), and `dco-rollout-evidence.md` (historical). The\nother historical docs (`88ab-feature-branch-evidence.md`, `bash-migration.md`) ARE already\nlinked, just not labeled as historical.\n\n## Decision: label-in-place, NO git-mv (resolves the plan-review E2/T7/E4/G1G2 findings)\nThe audit floated \"and/or move historical files under `docs/archive/`\". **We deliberately\nchoose NOT to relocate any file.** Rationale: the inbound-link blast radius of moving these\nfiles is large and cross-cutting — `bash-migration.md` alone is referenced by 8-10 `src/rebar/`\nproduction docstrings, the root `README.md`, `docs/oss-comparison-and-remediation.md`, and\ntest files; `88ab-feature-branch-evidence.md` is referenced by\n`infra/gerrit/feature-branch-e2e-scenarios.sh`. A `git-mv` would silently break all of these\nfor near-zero reader benefit. Instead, historical docs stay at their current paths and are\ngrouped under a clearly-labeled **\"Historical evidence\"** section in the index. No file\nmoves ⇒ no inbound link can break.\n\n## Scope\n- Add index entries for the 3 living/normative unlinked docs (`attest-substrate.md`,\n  `review-policy.md`, `session-id-shims.md`) under the appropriate living-reference/policy\n  buckets.\n- Add a clearly-labeled **\"Historical evidence\"** section to the index and list the\n  historical docs there (`dco-rollout-evidence.md` — currently unlinked, add it;\n  `88ab-feature-branch-evidence.md` and `bash-migration.md` — move their LISTING into this\n  section, files stay put).\n- Add a short taxonomy note at the top of the index defining the buckets: **living\n  reference / policy / design rationale / historical evidence** — so future docs land in\n  the right place.\n- Do NOT git-mv or move any file; do NOT edit any inbound links (nothing moves).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] The 3 living/normative docs are each linked EXACTLY ONCE from the index\n      (verify, prints nothing):\n      `for b in attest-substrate.md review-policy.md session-id-shims.md; do [ \"$(grep -cF \"($b)\" docs/README.md)\" = 1 ] || echo \"BAD $b\"; done`\n- [ ] The 3 historical docs are each linked EXACTLY ONCE (so the old Contributor\n      entries for bash-migration.md / 88ab-feature-branch-evidence.md were MOVED, not\n      duplicated) AND appear under the \"Historical evidence\" heading (verify, prints\n      nothing for both loops):\n      `for b in dco-rollout-evidence.md 88ab-feature-branch-evidence.md bash-migration.md; do [ \"$(grep -cF \"($b)\" docs/README.md)\" = 1 ] || echo \"DUP/MISSING $b\"; done`\n      and\n      `for b in dco-rollout-evidence.md 88ab-feature-branch-evidence.md bash-migration.md; do awk '/^#+ *Historical evidence/{h=1} h' docs/README.md | grep -qF \"($b)\" || echo \"NOT-IN-SECTION $b\"; done`\n      (`grep -cF` is a LITERAL count — no regex/dot-escaping issues; `=1` catches both\n      a missing link and a duplicate left behind in Contributor, closing the G6 gap.)\n- [ ] A \"Historical evidence\" section heading exists and a brief taxonomy note defines\n      the four buckets (verify, prints nothing):\n      `grep -qi '^#\\+ *Historical evidence' docs/README.md || echo \"NO SECTION\"; for t in 'living reference' 'policy' 'design rationale' 'historical evidence'; do grep -qi \"$t\" docs/README.md || echo \"NO BUCKET: $t\"; done`\n- [ ] No file is relocated and no inbound link edited — only `docs/README.md` changes\n      (verify): `git status --porcelain -- docs/` shows exactly one ` M docs/README.md`\n      line and NO `R`/`D` (rename/delete) entries.\n\nFiles: `docs/README.md` (only)."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783822580216098001,"uuid":"92029b18-9435-42b9-a196-527970c969d5"}